
[1]indignity

   INDIG'NITY, n. [L. indignitas.] Unmerited, contemptuous conduct towards
   another; any action towards another which manifests contempt for him;
   contumely; incivility or injury, accompanied with insult. Contemptuous
   words respecting one, or foul language in the presence of persons of
   character and delicacy, and indecent behavior, are indignities. Christ
   on the cross was treated with the foulest indignity.
